metadata.name: hash cats – genesis #300
metadata.description:
Mono was your typical countryside cat. During one late-night prowl, Mono discovered The Hash. All the other cats were astonished by the beauty of the thrilling find. Not before long did all the cats find themself living in the vibrant New Hash City. To keep up with the constant adrenaline rush of their new life, the cats have developed several traits to help them master the city.

hash cats are a group of 512 generated cats with numerous different features.

Rarity features include:
– 9 head colors
– 32 different head-gears
– 46 collars
– 40 upper face traits (eyewear and makeup)
– 3 lower face traits
– 15 mouth and nose types
– 46 sweaters and hoodies
– 81 sweater traits
– 3 gaze directions
– 29 background patterns * 30 swatch variations
– A very small chance to mint a cat with an artist signature

~ 1% chance to mint a Mono cat

hash cats is a collaboration GENTK by @levoontin & @3amkind.

Type 's' to save a PNG image of your cat (in full screen).

 → Follow @hash_cats_ on Twitter for updates on the cats!

metadata.name: Chord Unknown #229
metadata.description:
The feeling of experimenting with an instrument you have not learned, and then suddenly striking an actual chord.

The code creates several grids and then applies one of six unique deformation techniques with varying intensity. It's a defined process of experimentation, and even though I'm the one that wrote the rules, each output breaks through somehow as a complete surprise to me. So when I see them, I get a Chord Unknown.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Drifters #46
metadata.description:
In an undiscovered area, you've stumbled upon an unknown creature.
It looks weirdly haunting, and you're feeling a sense of unease.

You're wondering what it's doing.

It seems to move in patterns, and sometimes suddenly changes course.
Is it communicating?

(to whom?)

Setting aside your discomfort for a moment, you're realizing you could be seeing it wrong.
While the creature does look eerie and its motivations are unclear,
you realize every culture has its own appreciation of aesthetics,
and you can't help noticing there is a certain grace to this performance.

And it all makes sense.

You're witnessing uncharted explorations of elegance.

–

Append [?scale=<number>] to the url to scale the renderer.
Press [control / command + s] to save the current frame to a file.

© 2022 Monokai.

metadata.name: In the Edge #298
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.

metadata.name: Rehash 10000 #472
metadata.description:
This project was supposed to be released in celebration of fxhash reaching 10,000 projects since its inception, but it's hard to celebrate when war breaks out and innocent people fear for their lives. Please go ahead and mint as many iterations as you like for free. If you feel the art is worth more than 0 tez, you are welcome to donate to the Tezos fund to support our Ukrainian friends (KT1DWnLiUkNtAQDErXxudFEH63JC6mqg3HEx).

Each mint combines 5 of my previous 14 fxhash projects into a drug-induced distorted vision of life in the Metaverse. This artwork is fully generative and was entirely hand-coded in 5333 lines of plain JavaScript code. Forever limited to 500 editions on the Tezos blockchain. London, February 2022.

metadata.name: Your Octo-Valentine #9
metadata.description:
Happy Valentine's Day everyone! it's a giveaway time!

The day before yesterday was my birthday and now I'm glad to to make a gift to my friends and collectors here. I wish this small octopus will add a bit more warm vibes to your day : )

Here you can encounter a valentine card, with a generous octopus presenting:
- cupcakes🧁
- cheesecakes
- ice cream🍦
- muffins
- roses and flowers🌹
- lollipops🍭
- grapes and figs🍇
- latte macchiato and champagne🥂

And don't forget about the octocat!

Artwork is based on JPG layers (with masks), vqgan+clip, python and p5.js code.
